  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduction stunting of the children in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will create a piece of evidence to reduce the stunting of 1200 malnourished under 5 years of children in the northern &amp; southern parts of Bangladesh, providing Nutrition Education (NE) &amp; demonstrations of nutrient-based homemade recipes through the Mother Support Group in the community.  NE strategy will be based on the nutrition triangle model proposed by UNICEF i.e. food security, caring practices, disease control. Groups of mothers &amp; caregivers of the children will be trained.</narrative>
  </description>
